Adds a deterministic terminal-log wrapper workflow for agent handoff without copy-and-paste.

Implemented:
- ./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>
- ./ns terminal-status
- ./ns terminal-upload
- terminal log pointer: docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt
- terminal log module and tests
- Action Registry metadata for terminal-log commands
- documentation for PASS/FAIL handoff semantics

Workflow semantics:
- d = PASS seen, continue using committed/pushed terminal log
- f/fail = FAIL seen, terminal log uploaded, analyze committed log
- manual copy-and-paste is only required if terminal-upload itself fails

Safety boundary:
- terminal-status is read-only
- run-logged is local-only and writes terminal logs
- terminal-upload may commit/push only docs/reports/terminal artifacts
- terminal-upload refuses dirty non-log files

